  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: For Request transaction screen now we do not have any field validation. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n1. iOS/Android:\r\n\r\nCurrently max length of the amount: 15 characters including separator (./,). This is different from the amount user can type for /send command in chat. It should be consistent in both places and seems like Wallet is a place to adjust:\r\n1.1 Expected: Amount before separator - seems like can be of any length or I can't find the limit\r\n1.2 Expected: Amount after separator - should be not more than 18 digits after comma (e.g 0.123456789012345678). Currently, it's possible to enter only 13 digits after comma (e.g. 0.1234567890123)\r\n1.3 \"0\" is now not allowed as a sum to send. In some cases, it's valid to send \"0\" (e.g https://contribute.status.im/sgt.html ), so it should be fine to request it too.\r\n1.4 I can send request with empty amount field / invalid data in the field - should not allow to proceed to another screen as there is no sense in it\r\n\r\n",
